* chore: pass watchdog ip address to dev server process

Dev server monitors watchdog port on localhost to be sure that Java process
is running, otherwise it kills itself.
It could happend that Java and Node processes resolve localhost ip
address differently (ipv4 vs ipv6), for example when using Node 17 and
setting Java system property `-Djava.net.preferIPv4Stack=true`.
This change resolves the ip address in Java process and provides it to
the node process so it will bind to the correct address.', 'distinct': False, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/vaadin/flow/commits/88784100b5f69621ad8aa4037561f1c961579e76'}, {'sha': 'ef9252c82811558f44f86007e23157fd03d55b47', 'author': {'email': '31067185+ZheSun88@users.noreply.github.com', 'name': 'Zhe Sun'}, 'message': 'chore: revert the pull request target changes', 'distinct': False, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/vaadin/flow/commits/ef9252c82811558f44f86007e23157fd03d55b47'}, {'sha': '897915b5a9c266d8f31c30a9c78fc9020614189d', 'author': {'email': 'zhe@vaadin.com', 'name': 'Zhe Sun'}, 'message': "Merge branch 'master' into revert-13532-dependabot/maven/io.swagger.codegen.v3-swagger-codegen-3.0.34", 'distinct': True, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/vaadin/flow/commits/897915b5a9c266d8f31c30a9c78fc9020614189d'}]}
